{# English clinical interpretation templates #}

{# Clinical interpretation based on dysbiosis category #}
{% macro clinical_interpretation(dysbiosis_category, dysbiosis_index) %}
{% if dysbiosis_category == 'normal' %}
<div class="clinical-interpretation normal">
    <p><strong>Normal Microbiome Balance:</strong> The analysis indicates a healthy and balanced gut microbiome. The dysbiosis index of {{ "%.1f"|format(dysbiosis_index) }} falls within the normal range (â‰¤20), suggesting optimal microbial diversity and composition.</p>
    
    <p>The phylum distribution shows appropriate proportions of beneficial bacteria, with adequate representation of key bacterial groups essential for digestive health and immune function.</p>
    
    <p><strong>Clinical Significance:</strong> This balanced microbiome profile supports healthy digestion, nutrient absorption, and immune system function. The horse appears to have a stable microbial ecosystem that contributes to overall gut health.</p>
</div>
{% elif dysbiosis_category == 'mild' %}
<div class="clinical-interpretation mild">
    <p><strong>Mild Microbiome Imbalance:</strong> The analysis reveals a mild disruption in the gut microbiome balance. The dysbiosis index of {{ "%.1f"|format(dysbiosis_index) }} indicates moderate microbial imbalance (21-50 range).</p>
    
    <p>While the overall microbial community remains functional, there are detectable shifts in bacterial populations that may affect digestive efficiency and immune response.</p>
    
    <p><strong>Clinical Significance:</strong> This mild imbalance may be associated with recent dietary changes, mild stress, or environmental factors. Early intervention through dietary management and probiotic support may help restore optimal balance.</p>
</div>
{% else %}
<div class="clinical-interpretation severe">
    <p><strong>Significant Microbiome Disruption:</strong> The analysis indicates substantial disruption of the gut microbiome. The dysbiosis index of {{ "%.1f"|format(dysbiosis_index) }} suggests severe microbial imbalance (>50), requiring veterinary attention.</p>
    
    <p>The microbial community shows significant alterations in key bacterial populations, which may compromise digestive function, nutrient absorption, and immune system effectiveness.</p>
    
    <p><strong>Clinical Significance:</strong> This level of dysbiosis may be associated with gastrointestinal disorders, systemic illness, antibiotic treatment, or significant dietary/environmental stressors. Comprehensive veterinary evaluation and targeted intervention are recommended.</p>
</div>
{% endif %}
{% endmacro %}

{# Phylum-specific clinical notes #}
{% macro phylum_clinical_notes(phylum_name, percentage, ref_min, ref_max) %}
{% set status = 'normal' if percentage >= ref_min and percentage <= ref_max else ('low' if percentage < ref_min else 'high') %}

{% if phylum_name == 'Bacillota' %}
    {% if status == 'low' %}
    <p><strong>Bacillota ({{ "%.1f"|format(percentage) }}%):</strong> Below optimal range. Low levels may indicate reduced fiber fermentation capacity and potential digestive inefficiency.</p>
    {% elif status == 'high' %}
    <p><strong>Bacillota ({{ "%.1f"|format(percentage) }}%):</strong> Elevated levels. May suggest dietary imbalance or inflammatory conditions affecting gut environment.</p>
    {% else %}
    <p><strong>Bacillota ({{ "%.1f"|format(percentage) }}%):</strong> Within normal range, supporting healthy fiber digestion and short-chain fatty acid production.</p>
    {% endif %}
{% elif phylum_name == 'Bacteroidota' %}
    {% if status == 'low' %}
    <p><strong>Bacteroidota ({{ "%.1f"|format(percentage) }}%):</strong> Lower than expected. May affect complex carbohydrate breakdown and vitamin synthesis.</p>
    {% elif status == 'high' %}
    <p><strong>Bacteroidota ({{ "%.1f"|format(percentage) }}%):</strong> Elevated levels. Could indicate dietary changes or gut environment shifts.</p>
    {% else %}
    <p><strong>Bacteroidota ({{ "%.1f"|format(percentage) }}%):</strong> Optimal levels support efficient nutrient processing and metabolic balance.</p>
    {% endif %}
{% elif phylum_name == 'Pseudomonadota' %}
    {% if status == 'high' %}
    <p><strong>Pseudomonadota ({{ "%.1f"|format(percentage) }}%):</strong> Elevated levels may indicate inflammatory processes or environmental stress.</p>
    {% else %}
    <p><strong>Pseudomonadota ({{ "%.1f"|format(percentage) }}%):</strong> Within acceptable range.</p>
    {% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% endmacro %}

{# Overall assessment summary #}
{% macro overall_assessment(dysbiosis_category) %}
<div class="overall-assessment">
    {% if dysbiosis_category == 'normal' %}
    <h4>Overall Assessment: Healthy Microbiome</h4>
    <p>The comprehensive analysis indicates a well-balanced and healthy gut microbiome that supports optimal digestive function and overall health.</p>
    {% elif dysbiosis_category == 'mild' %}
    <h4>Overall Assessment: Monitor and Support</h4>
    <p>The microbiome shows mild imbalance that can typically be addressed through dietary management and supportive care.</p>
    {% else %}
    <h4>Overall Assessment: Requires Intervention</h4>
    <p>Significant microbiome disruption requires veterinary evaluation and comprehensive treatment approach to restore gut health.</p>
    {% endif %}
</div>
{% endmacro %}